race.comment: EARL OF BANTRY (5) resumes for a top metro yard seeking the hat-trick off an all the way win in an Open 3 at Newcastle. He's has a stable switch and has won 2/4 fresh. He's trialled well and draws to advantage. The one to beat. INNERVISIONS (17) is also in good hands and improved again beaten 1.2L in a CL2 at the Gold Coast. Carries 3kg less in this grade, and that brings him into it. BIG BOY GEORGE (10) resumes for the Currie yard and is also good enough to consider. He's trialled well at the Sunshine Coast and goes on the fresh side. MISHANI RENEGADE (8) showed enough last time at the Sunshine Coast to consider.
